cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper proposes a method to build a neural network that is similar to an ensemble of decision trees. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of activation functions and thresholds, which are commonly used in neural networks, indicating that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The experiments involve datasets related to computer vision (cs.CV) and the paper discusses the use of fully connected layers (cs.NE), further supporting these sub-categories. Finally, decision trees are a common tool in data science (cs.DS), making this sub-category also a possibility.
